# Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

## Backend

### Database
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:password@localhost:5432/freedomtalk"

### Redis
REDIS_URL="redis://localhost:6379"

### LiveKit (Mediasoup) - Not used for Discord clone
# LIVEKIT_URL="ws://localhost:7880"
# LIVEKIT_API_KEY="devkey"
# LIVEKIT_API_SECRET="devsecret"

### S3 (Hetzner Object Storage)
S3_ENDPOINT="https://fsn1.your-objectstorage.com"
S3_ACCESS_KEY="your_access_key_here"
S3_SECRET_KEY="your_secret_key_here"
S3_BUCKET="freedomtalk"
S3_REGION="default"

### NextAuth
NEXTAUTH_SECRET="your_random_secret_here_min_32_chars"
NEXTAUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

### OAuth Providers (Optional)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=""
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=""
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=""
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=""

### Rate Limits
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000
RATE_LIMIT_MAX_REQUESTS=100

### JWT
JWT_SECRET="your_jwt_secret_here"
JWT_EXPIRES_IN="1h"
REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRES_IN="7d"

## Frontend

### API
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL="http://localhost:3000/api/v1"
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL="ws://localhost:3000/socket.io"

### LiveKit
# NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEKIT_URL="wss://localhost:7880"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_LIVEKIT_ROOM_PREFIX="room-"

---

## Notes

1. Generate secure random secrets using: `openssl rand -base64 32` or `node -e "console.log(crypto.randomBytes(32).toString('base64'))"`
2. For production, use environment variables, not commit them
3. Never commit `.env` file (add to .gitignore)
4. Use different secrets for development and production
5. Rotate JWT secrets periodically
